<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2012/11/16/killer-of-sheep/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Killer of Sheep">Killer of Sheep</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p><a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/Aaron-kills-sheep3.gif"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2804" title="Aaron kills sheep3" src="http://blog.ninapaley.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/Aaron-kills-sheep3.gif" alt="Exodus 29" width="640" height="360" /></a></p>
<p>Maybe the timing&#8217;s not good on this, given current events. This is LITERALLY about Hebrews and sheep, per Exodus. It is not a political statement.</p>
<p>Here is Aharon, following God&#8217;s commandments per <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/108/02/29.html" target="_blank">Exodus 29</a>. Exodus is a pretty depressing read. Last night when I animated this, I found it depressing. This morning I found it kind of funny. Cartoon violence is magical that way.</p>
<p>Full text of <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/108/02/29.html" target="_blank">Exodus 29</a> (King James version) after the fold: <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2012/11/16/killer-of-sheep/#more-2803" class="more-link">Continue reading Killer of Sheep</a></p>
